Intepretations for party allocations under coalition may vary among sources. One of PBRS Candidates contested in an area where it did not seek approval from parent coalition, BN. There is a presence for missing data points for age attribute for candidates.

Corretions were made on Individual Candidate Vote for Seats of Bachok, Pasir Puteh, Tanah Merah, Tambun, Ipoh Timor, Indera Mahkota, Hulu Langat, Seremban, Port Dickson, Tangga Batu, Segamat and Papar
Correction was made for Total Valid Votes for Seat of Batu
Correction was made for winner for Maran and party association for Dato' Sri Haji Ismail bin Haji Abd. Muttalib
Correction was made for winner for Hulu Selangor
Correction was made for winner for Gua Musang
Correction was made for winner for Kepala Batas
Correction was made for winner for Beluran as Roland Kiandee gone against GRS-BN deal and Roland Kiandee opted to go under PN (with an understanding Bersatu is part of GRS and PN)
Correction was made for winner for Kota Marudu
Correction was made for party association of Poyne B. Tudus @ Patrick Payne
There is a dispute for Party Membership of these four individuals under GRS Coalition: DATUK ARMIZAN BIN MOHD ALI, KHAIRUL FIRDAUS AKBAR KHAN, JONATHAN YASIN and DATUK MATBALI BIN MUSAH
Shahidan Kassim contested as PN - direct candidate, only considered entering PAS after his election victory.
Dato' Sri Haji Ismail bin Haji Abd. Muttalib joined PAS one day before nomination
